
[1]polverine

   POL'VERINE, n. [L. pulvis, dust.] The calcined ashes of a plant, of the
   nature of pot and pearl ashes, brought from the Levant and Syria. In
   the manufacture of glass, it is preferred to other ashes, as the glass
   made with it is perfectly white.
